If you're gonna have a relationship with God, it is only done through full submission.

25:30.114 --> 25:36.384
And if you're gonna have a healthy marriage, a healthy marriage is found in mutual submission.

25:37.205 --> 25:43.695
The Apostle Paul in Ephesians 5.21 says submit one to another out of reverence for Christ.

25:44.957 --> 25:51.126
But you do know that if you're not first fully submitted to God, there is no way on earth you will submit to your spouse.

25:52.348 --> 25:53.129
It's just logical.

25:53.169 --> 25:58.898
If I can't submit to a perfect God and I'm gonna turn around submit to an imperfect spouse, it's not gonna happen.

25:59.266 --> 26:03.851
So if you're not first submitted to God, you will not submit to your spouse.

26:05.792 --> 26:16.843
But there's a step before that that Abraham demonstrates, if you don't first believe that God will provide, you're also not gonna submit to God.

26:18.145 --> 26:24.251
Abraham was fully convinced that God would provide what God said he would provide, which is why Abraham was willing to submit.

26:25.532 --> 26:27.634
If you are not fully convinced

26:27.842 --> 26:35.731
that God can provide everything you need in your life and in your marriage, you won't submit to God.

26:35.971 --> 26:39.435
And if you won't submit to God, there's no way you'll ever submit to your spouse.

26:40.696 --> 26:49.726
So many of us have relational problems in our marriage because we have provisional doubts in our relationship with God, which is preventing us from first submitting to God.

26:51.668 --> 26:53.650
The provision came after the submission.

26:54.530 --> 27:04.589
Which washes, imagine, imagine for a minute if you really believed God could provide everything that you think you need in your marriage for you.

27:06.273 --> 27:15.410
If you really believe that, it would probably be better for you to spend a bunch of time wearing God out in prayer

27:15.650 --> 27:24.179
about what you want out of your spouse, about how you wish your spouse would change, about what you want less of from your spouse, about what you want your spouse to improve.

27:24.519 --> 27:31.926
It will probably serve you better if you wore God out in prayer, if you believed he would provide it, then you do nagging your spouse to try to get it.

27:36.431 --> 27:43.698
But if you don't first believe that God can provide that, you won't submit to God and you'll never submit

27:43.778 --> 27:45.521
to your spouse, it just doesn't happen.

27:45.541 --> 27:50.628
That's why I love the 14th verse that says Abraham called the place the Lord will provide.

27:52.230 --> 27:56.196
And the mountain is it will be provided.

27:57.298 --> 28:03.928
If you don't first believe that, if you're not convinced that God will provide anything, everything, you will not submit to your spouse for anything.

28:03.948 --> 28:04.528
You just won't.

28:06.251 --> 28:07.453
And I'm speaking from experience.

28:07.473 --> 28:08.835
I've been married almost 30 years.

28:10.037 --> 28:11.058
I don't want to submit

28:11.138 --> 28:14.262
to somebody I don't feel like is doing what I need them to do.

28:15.664 --> 28:22.332
But if I know God will provide, then I can submit to Him and I can submit in my marriage.

28:22.472 --> 28:29.241
And then I don't have to control, I don't have to manipulate, I don't have to try to squeeze out of my spouse what I desire.

28:30.242 --> 28:30.683
Singles.

28:33.867 --> 28:39.474
If you don't like to submit, say it with me, don't get married.

28:40.258 --> 28:54.382
Listen, I would say if you are seriously dating somebody and moving towards marriage, I would absolutely make sure that this person has a pattern of submission and accountability to others.

28:55.124 --> 28:56.466
Because if they don't,

28:57.058 --> 29:05.931
You will be one of the people that sits in my office trying to work on their marriage by themselves because their spouse is unwilling to go to counseling or be accountable to anybody.

29:06.352 --> 29:13.904
I would ask of, if I was moving towards marriage with somebody, I would ask, hey, who are you accountable to and who do you submit to in your life?

29:14.244 --> 29:15.506
And give me some examples.

29:16.354 --> 29:28.513
And then at some point I would want to meet those people so I can look those people in the eye and go give me some examples of when you had to call them into account because they had wrong thinking, they were out of line, they had wrong behavior, and how did they respond?

29:28.573 --> 29:36.165
Because what they did there will give me a good indication of whether or not they will ever be willing to submit in a marriage.

29:36.205 --> 29:39.250
You don't find that out after you get married, you find that out before.

29:39.350 --> 29:40.973
So marriage is a place of submission.

29:41.033 --> 29:44.338
Number three, marriage is a place of service.

29:45.378 --> 29:48.643
In Leviticus, chapter six, verses eight through 13, it says this.

29:49.344 --> 29:52.929
The Lord said to Moses, give Aaron and his sons this command.

29:53.751 --> 29:55.934
These are the regulations for the burn offering.

29:55.954 --> 30:04.146
The burn offering is to remain on the altar hearth throughout the night till morning and the fire must be kept burning on the altar.

30:04.706 --> 30:09.372
Then he goes on to say, the priest shall put on linen clothes with linen undergarments next to his body.

30:09.412 --> 30:14.559
He removes the ashes of the burn offering that the fire consumed and he places those beside the altar.

30:15.060 --> 30:20.267
Then that places, then he takes those clothes off, puts on others, carries the ashes outside to a camp.

30:20.327 --> 30:22.890
That places ceremonial clean verse 12.

30:24.032 --> 30:27.216
The fire on the altar must be kept burning.

30:27.276 --> 30:28.818
It must not go out.

30:29.090 --> 30:35.939
Every morning the priest is to add firewood and arrange to burn offering on the fire and burn of the fat of the fellowship offerings on it.

30:36.300 --> 30:41.887
Verse 13, the fire must be kept burning on the altar continuously.

30:41.927 --> 30:44.130
It must not go out.

30:44.230 --> 30:48.997
Three times in five verses we are told, the fire must not go out.

30:49.077 --> 30:51.000
It must keep burning.

30:51.040 --> 30:52.321
That's marriage.

30:53.663 --> 30:55.826
Marriage is a continual work.

30:56.450 --> 31:01.442
of two people serving one another so that the marriage fire never goes out.

31:02.464 --> 31:07.216
And when I say marriage fire, I'm not talking about passion, romance, that's nice too.

31:07.717 --> 31:14.834
I'm talking about the little things that we do for each other day in, day out, because we are here to serve one another.

31:16.834 --> 31:19.417
It's the roles and responsibilities you have.

31:19.898 --> 31:21.821
It's keeping the commitments that you made.

31:21.881 --> 31:24.344
It's finishing the things you committed to doing.

31:24.765 --> 31:26.387
It's taking care of the chores.

31:26.727 --> 31:29.130
It's asking, can I get you a drink?

31:29.150 --> 31:33.857
It's asking, is there anything I can take off your shoulders that would relieve stress from your life?

31:33.977 --> 31:37.001
It's date night, it's taking a walk, it's conversations.

31:37.602 --> 31:39.605
The fire must not go out.

31:39.885 --> 31:43.730
Marriage is a process of continually serving one another.

31:46.594 --> 31:55.705
I've worked with a lot of couples over a lot of years, and I can tell you with all honesty, the primary reasons that marriages don't work out are not infidelity.

31:55.725 --> 31:57.307
They're not financial fights.

31:57.387 --> 31:58.829
They're not parenting issues.

31:59.810 --> 32:09.842
It's two people who stopped fulfilling their responsibility to serve one another day in, day out in all the little things.

32:11.266 --> 32:13.829
That's what leads to the disconnection.

32:13.890 --> 32:16.573
That's what leads to the disillusionment, the hopelessness.

32:16.994 --> 32:20.118
That's what keeps us from doing the things that we need to do.

32:20.739 --> 32:24.404
The fire must not go out.

32:24.464 --> 32:26.687
You need to remember that, and that's all about serving.

32:27.628 --> 32:28.089
Singles.

32:31.253 --> 32:34.838
If you don't like serving, that'll give Mary.

32:36.180 --> 32:38.002
Listen, I would say if somebody

32:38.114 --> 32:52.511
If somebody pressed me and said, hey, someone's getting married, give me only two non-negotiables they need to look for in a spouse, I would absolutely say you need to look for somebody that has a pattern of submission and accountability, and you need to look at somebody who has a pattern of service.

32:53.893 --> 32:59.459
Because if they've got those two things in their lives now, I know those two things are gonna show up in my marriage.

33:01.342 --> 33:04.946
And when I say a pattern of serving, I don't mean a pattern of serving you.

33:06.402 --> 33:08.566
That's the dating process, right?

33:08.606 --> 33:11.291
Part of the reason they're serving me, they may have a good heart.

33:11.892 --> 33:15.538
But part of the reason they're serving me is because they also are desiring something back for me.

33:17.021 --> 33:20.026
Me to serve them back, me to reciprocate, me to love them.

33:20.107 --> 33:28.722
When you know somebody has a heart and pattern to serve is when you see them serving somebody else consistently, who can do nothing for them?

33:29.506 --> 33:31.288
That's when you know they got a heart of service.

33:31.348 --> 33:32.990
So yeah, it's cute.

33:33.010 --> 33:34.432
They treat you like a queen.

33:34.472 --> 33:35.353
Yeah, that's cute.

33:35.433 --> 33:35.934
I got that.

33:36.334 --> 33:40.600
But does he serve other people who can't do anything for him?

33:40.700 --> 33:42.242
That's a heart of service.

33:42.282 --> 33:46.407
That's when you know somebody is there and somebody can serve.

33:46.527 --> 33:47.869
I would absolutely look for that.

33:47.889 --> 33:53.656
So the altar is always been and always will be a place of service.

33:56.019 --> 33:58.482
So your marriage needs to be

33:58.626 --> 34:03.733
a place of sacrifice, a place of submission, and a place of service.

34:04.715 --> 34:10.563
And if it's not, you have got the wrong perspective on what you committed to.

34:10.623 --> 34:20.758
And if you're thinking about getting married one day, and those three things are not top of mind to you, you've got the wrong perspective on what you're signing up for.

34:21.399 --> 34:22.601
So here's your homework for the week.

34:22.621 --> 34:26.386
I can give you homework because I'm coming back next week to check.

34:26.946 --> 34:28.288
Here's your homework, married couples.

34:28.568 --> 34:33.675
I want you to evaluate your marriage and how you are showing up in your marriage in these three areas.

34:34.396 --> 34:43.930
Give yourself a little one to five ranking on and then ask your spouse what they think your ranking is because that'll lower the curve a little bit and probably average out where you should be.

34:44.971 --> 34:48.576
But are these evident in your marriage and if they're not, what can you do?

34:48.636 --> 34:49.638
What can you do?

34:49.678 --> 34:55.506
One thing this week that you can begin to do to serve or to sacrifice or to submit

34:55.842 --> 34:57.605
in a way you've not been doing in singles.

34:59.108 --> 35:00.711
I want you to evaluate your own character.

35:01.312 --> 35:10.569
When I hear these words, when I hear Eric say, if you don't like to serve, don't get married, it is my first inclination.

35:11.070 --> 35:11.972
I ain't getting married then.

35:13.414 --> 35:15.538
Or is it maybe I need to cultivate

35:15.714 --> 35:19.762
this in my life because I believe Christians should walk in these characteristics.

35:19.983 --> 35:33.089
Marriage or no marriage, as Christians we should be the kind of people who sacrifice, who are willing to submit one to another, who are willing to serve one another out of reverence for Christ and out of our relationship with Christ.

35:33.570 --> 35:36.937
That's your homework this week and I want to pray for you and get out of your way.

35:36.997 --> 35:37.618
Father,

35:39.394 --> 35:47.769
Thank you for giving us a new perspective or maybe reminding us on the proper perspective of what marriage is all about.

35:48.831 --> 35:52.116
The wedding took place and the marriage began at the altar.

35:52.437 --> 36:04.498
And God, if we're gonna walk out marriage in a way that honors you, it's gotta be represented by the same things that show up on the altar, sacrifice, submission, service.

36:05.058 --> 36:16.773
Father, we need Your strength to do it, so I pray that You would empower every person in the room to lean first into You in order to have the power to do what You've called them to do in their marriage.

36:17.474 --> 36:25.524
Father, for any marriages that may be struggling today, God, I pray that You would just give them hope that things could be different if they would just do some things different.

36:26.385 --> 36:33.394
Father, help us to live lives that give glory to You and help us live out marriages.

36:34.370 --> 36:36.310
they give glory to the world around us.

36:36.411 --> 36:37.522
In Jesus' name, amen.

